Chinese newspaper should be "reformed" after call
A Chinese newspaper, which had called for the release of a reporter on the front page, which had been accused of defamation, should be reformed, told a press regulator.
The Guangzhou-based New Express had printed a rare public appeal for the release of the journalist Chen Yongzhou.
But Chen was later on television that he had accepted bribes to falsify reports on a portion of state company.
Now the New Express will be subjected to a "comprehensive Rektifizierung", the regulator said.
